nt|Zia Mahmood has the reputation (which he fully deserves) of being one of the trickiest and most creative bridge players in the history of the game. This week's deal is a good example of the type of magic that Zia is capable of at the bridge table. This deal was from the final round of the 2001 Cap Gemini when Zia and Andrew faced ^*BKrzysztof Jassem^*N and ^*BPiotr Tuszynski^*N of Poland. Jassem-Tuszynski are one of the great partnerships in the world today. Last week's deal was played by Jassem in the 2001 Cap Gemini. If you have not seen last week's deal yet you should definitely have a look after you have finished with this week's deal!

At the time that this week's deal was played, Zia and Andrew held a slim lead over Americans ^*BHoward Weinstein^*N and ^*BSteve Garner^*N in the standings of the Cap Gemini. The 12 IMP swing that went to Zia and Andrew on this deal was critical in allowing the defending champions to hold on to first place. This deal has been rotated to make South the declarer.

